      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Risk Owner Assignment and Mitigation Tracking"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A risk entry without a named owner is an unmanaged risk. Risk ownership is the mechanism by which accountability for monitoring, controlling, and reporting a specific risk is formally allocated to a person with the authority and resources to act on it. Mitigation tracking then converts that accountability into a time-bounded programme of work with checkpoints, so that the steering committee can see whether risks are trending toward closure or stagnating."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Risk mitigation tracking lifecycle: Identified → Owner Assigned → Treatment Plan → Controls In Progress → Mitigated/Accepted, with quarterly review loop and incident re-open path",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The lifecycle above has two feedback paths. The quarterly review loop re-scores every open risk and updates control status, causing some risks to advance to mitigated while others are pushed back when controls are found ineffective. The incident re-open path reactivates a previously mitigated risk when an incident demonstrates the controls have failed."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Owner Assignment by Risk Category"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Assign primary ownership to the role with operational authority over the controls, not the role with the most seniority. An executive who cannot directly instruct engineers to implement a technical control cannot meaningfully own that risk."
          }
        ]
      },
