          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Risk owner assignment connects each register entry to a named role with operational authority and an accountable executive. A treatment plan documents which of the four options (mitigate, accept, transfer, avoid) has been chosen, the specific actions required, their owners, and their due dates. Overdue action detection automates escalation before governance gaps accumulate. The quarterly review report generated from the tracking database gives the AI Steering Committee a real-time picture of risk portfolio health rather than a snapshot that was accurate only on the day it was written."
